# Internal Link Formatting Rules

1. Use backslashes (`\`) for directory separators in internal links
2. Include trailing backslashes (`\`) in internal links
3. Use the pipe (`|`) syntax for link text: `[[path\to\file\|Display Text]]`

## Examples:
- Correct: `[[Java\Java\|Java]]`
- Correct: `[[Philosophy\Personal Views\|Personal Views]]`
- Incorrect: `[[Java/Java|Java]]` (forward slashes)
- Incorrect: `[[Java\Java|Java]]` (missing trailing slash) 